&lt;h1&gt;Access Supervisor&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surgery are looking to appointment an Access Supervisor on a permenant basis to join the their team (to act as liaison between the clinical teams, the corporate functions that support patient pathways and directly support the senior management team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be experienced in the use of PAS and have an excellent understanding of  the referral to treatment  (RTT) pathway for surgical patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Access Manager this role will allow you manage through validation processes,  the 18 week pathways for patients within the speciality for these services.  You will be flexible in your approach to meeting deadlines and like interaction with a wide variety of staff within the hospital. You will be responsible for all Inpatients fuctions for select sub–speacilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 20th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
